<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>take someone at his word • take someone’s word</xh5><p> <i>take someone at his word—</i>assume that smb. means what he says and act accordingly, even if he may not have quite meant it: I was joking, but he <u>took me at my word</u> and arrived with a bag of sliced pork and herbs.</p><p> <i>take someone’s word</i>—(also: take someone’s word for it) believe a person even though there is no proof that what he says is true: I don’t expect any of you to <u>take my word</u> blindly. Read the suggested articles and books.</p> </entry>
